# --- Callisto source ---
# The broad secret-guard globs above (**/*key*, **/*token*, **/*private*, *seed*, etc.)
# would otherwise swallow legitimate source files in this wallet codebase
# (token.go, key.go, seed.go, private.go, keystore.go, ...). Re-include all
# project source and module metadata. These come last so they win.
!**/*.go
!go.mod
!go.sum
!**/*.json
# The release-signing PUBLIC key is embedded into the binary (updater trust root)
# and is safe/required to commit; the broad `**/*key*` guard would otherwise hide
# it. The matching PRIVATE key lives outside the repo and is never committed.
!internal/updater/release_pubkey.ed25519
# The keystore *source* package is a directory named "keystore", which the
# broad `keystore/` guard above excludes; git won't apply the *.go negations to
# files inside an excluded directory, so re-include the source dir explicitly.
# (Real keystore *data* lives in the OS config dir, never in the repo.)
!internal/keystore/
# Same reasoning: the keystore-recover diagnostic tool's directory name matches
# *keystore* too.
!cmd/keystore-recover/
# ...but never let a real secrets/keystore directory back in.
/.local/
/keystore/
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
# The built binary at repo root only — anchored so it does NOT match the
# cmd/callisto/ source directory.
/callisto
/dist/
# Locally-installed fyne packaging CLI (see the Makefile `tools` target).
/bin/
# Note: BerkeleyMono font files ARE tracked (bundled/embedded under the project's
# indie license) — see internal/ui/fonts/.
